  "agent_output": "Done. Created a helper script for parsing XML deployment configs.\n\n**What I built:**\n\n- `skills/deployment/scripts/parse_xml.py` — Python script that reads XML files and extracts all `<setting>` elements, returning a dict of `name` → `value` pairs. Handles both `value` attributes and nested text.\n- `skills/deployment/scripts/parse_xml.sh` — Shell wrapper that makes it easy to call: `./parse_xml.sh <config.xml>`. It automatically picks up the skills directory location.\n- `skills/deployment/examples/deployment.xml` — Sample config showing deployment settings (host, port, auth, env, scaling, notifications).\n\n**Usage:**\n\n```bash\n# Via shell wrapper\n./skills/deployment/scripts/parse_xml.sh skills/deployment/examples/deployment.xml\n\n# Or directly in Python\npython3 skills/deployment/scripts/parse_xml.py skills/deployment/examples/deployment.xml\n```\n\nOutput prints each setting as `key=value`. The script also works for skills that generate configs dynamically.",
